
---
title: "Suitability of open-ocean instrumentation for use in near-field tsunami early warning along seismically active subduction zones"
collection: publications
permalink: /publications/Williamson_Newman_2019
#excerpt: ''
date: 2019-05-04
venue: 'Pure and Applied Geophysics'
paperurl: 'http://amy-l-williamson.github.io/files/Williamson_Newman_2019.pdf'
---

 In this study, we analyze the region surrounding four seismically active subduction zones, Cascadia, Japan, Chile, and Java, for their potential to facilitate local tsunami early warning using purely offshore direct tsunami observations.
[You can read this paper here.](http://amy-l-williamson.github.io/files/Williamson_Newmwan_2019.pdf)

Recommended citation:Williamson, A. L., & Newman, A. V. (2019). Suitability of open-ocean instrumentation for use in near-field tsunami early warning along seismically active subduction zones. Pure and Applied Geophysics, 176(7), 3247-3262.
